{
  "stem": "3964.3",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "For the first time, I saw a group of SS man [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] who were ordering the evacuation of the trains, of-- of the cars.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And there was one particular man there who stood out above all of 'em.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He was wearing a different type of a uniform, he's wearing a SS uniform, but he was wearing a different head gear, and he had his stars on his amulets or epaulets-- what is it?-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] which designated him to be a higher ranking officer.",
      "word_count": 48
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He also had a dog with him.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Someone approached him to ask questions, where we were and what was going on.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And after all, we were German citizens and we didn't-- didn't appreciate to be treated like he was treating us.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And he took out his gun, and he shot that man right through the head, straight through the head.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "That was our first experience of the SS [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] being as brutal as they turned out to be.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And he had a megaphone with him.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] he addressed us as [GERMAN].",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] That's you pigs, pig Jews.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "If you don't do what you're told to do, if you don't behave like you're expected to behave, what happened to this man right now, it's going to happen to all of you, so just do what you're told to do and nothing will happen to you.",
      "word_count": 47
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Where's our luggage?",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Looking around, we asked several people of the guards who were with us, who were on the trains.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Well, the luggage car where luggage was in had mechanical problems and we had to disconnect it from the train.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Your luggage is not here, but possibly we'll get it later on.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
